### How to activate

These are **not** auto-installed into your user-global `~/.cursor/` config, consistent with the kitchen policy (see `docs/DECISIONS.md` in the template source). Apply them once, manually:

```bash
./agent-guardrails/install.sh --with={{ _optional_ids | join(",") }}
```

Re-running `copier update` will regenerate this file if you change your answers, but **will not** re-run the `install.sh` command — that stays explicit.

Configure the required env vars in your shell (export in `~/.zshrc`, use a secret manager, etc.) before restarting Cursor.

